pageTitle: The E L E M E N T [Y] Era
pageDescription: After [X] was released, Jizza and I wanted to release another song in the [XYZ] trio. So the same night as [X] released I got started on another beat. I wanted to use a sample as an intro like a lot of Instagram prods were doing at the time, so I used another thing that was popular at the time; Alvin and the chipmunks getting cracked. So I started making the beat and it was sounding pretty good so I sent it to Jizza, and he thought it was good too so we decided to hop on it.

versions.name: [Y] V1
versions.description: The first version of [Y]. I had the intro planned and got some drums down but the mixing was very bad. This song was also made the same night that [X] released.

versions.name: [Y] V2
versions.description: The second version of [Y]. I did some more arrangement of the beat but it was still kinda buns.

versions.name: E L E M E N T [Y]
versions.description:
The second official release of the [XYZ] trio. This was recorded only 2 weeks after E L E M E N T [X] released. [Y] is considered the worst song out of the trilogy, it was sloppily made, poorly mixed, had clapped vocals, a corny intro, and bad mixing.
Not much to be said about this song, other than it took longer than [X] to finish, and the song cover was very lackluster.
